The paper deals with preventing attacks on anonymous data collection, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed mechanism involves rate-limiting rules, which can be seen as a data structure or algorithmic technique (cs.DS). The system is designed to work with existing data collection systems, which implies a connection to databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions empirical evaluation, which suggests a focus on machine learning or data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the proposed system involves deploying protection on existing systems, which implies a software engineering aspect (cs.SE).
